item.title: How to pronounce whilst
item.description: Is it pronounced Whilst or whilst? Break ‘whilst‘ down into sounds: [WYLST] – say it out loud and exaggerate the sounds until you can consistently produce them. Record yourself saying ‘whilst‘ in full sentences, then watch yourself and listen. How do you pronounce whilst in America? What does Whilst mean? item.description: Staying fit! item.title: Meet Jordan Foxworthy, the eldest daughter of Jeff Foxworthy.
item.description: Jordan Foxworthy is a member, a fundraiser, of the American non-profit making organization Compassion International. The organization helps to release children from poverty in Jesus's name. Foxworthy previously served as a campus administrator and ambassador of the Atlanta Mission. Besides the humanitarian works, Jordan is widely popular as the beloved daughter of famous American entertainment personality Jeff Foxworthy. Moreover, Jordan also works as an administrative assistant for her father's official website Foxworthy Outdoors.

item.title: Karl Miller, Founder and Ceo of Meridian Development, Killed in Saskatoon Crash
item.description: Deadly crash kills family of four; CEO of Meridian Development, Karl Miller, died in a crash along with his wife and two children. item.title: Russell Wilson's Ups and Downs Over the Years
item.description: Russell Wilson is no stranger to headlines — both good and bad — since joining the NFL in 2012. During his eight-year stint playing for the Seattle Seahawks, Wilson went through a divorce, tied the knot with Ciara, won a Super Bowl and became a father of kids Sienna and Win. The quarterback was later traded to the Denver Broncos in March 2022. While Wilson and Ciara’s family was on a high when she gave birth to their daughter, Amora, in December 2023, Wilson’s career took a hit that same month as he was benched for the remainder of the 2024 NFL season.

However, Tip says the moment wasn’t meant to be a diss aimed at the 6 God as he was simply reflecting on his late friend Terrance “Cap” Beasley. The ATL native rapped, “While I’m fightin’ my own, somehow got you home/So drunk in LA, end up pissin’ on Drake, shit/Fuck it, that’s still my brother.

item.title: Willow - Baby Name Meaning, Origin, and Popularity
item.description: Willow came into use as a given name after the willow tree, whose name was derived from the Old English word welig, meaning "willow." Willow trees are associated with grace and elegance, which gave way to the adjective "willowy." Other names with meanings related to willows include Arava, Willoughby, Dozier, Wellesley, Selby, and Salton. An ancient tree that figures in literature from Shakespeare to Harry Potter and is believed to possess magical powers, Willow is a lovely name, as graceful as its inspiration, that is growing in popularity along with Willa and Will.

item.description: Maggie Gyllenhaal, born on November 16, 1977, is an American actress and filmmaker. She comes from a family deeply involved in the film industry, with her parents being filmmakers Stephen Gyllenhaal and Naomi Achs, and her younger brother being actor Jake Gyllenhaal. Gyllenhaal started her career with minor roles in her father's films, and gained recognition for her role in the cult favorite Donnie Darko (2001), alongside her brother. She continued to showcase her talent in films like Adaptation, Confessions of a Dangerous Mind (both 2002), and Mona Lisa Smile (2003).

item.title: Lily-Rose Depp & 070 Shake Are Dating, Confirm With A Kiss: Photo Hollywood Life
item.description: Lily-Rose Depp and rapper 070 Shake (AKA Danielle Balbuena) are officially an item! The model/actress and daughter of Johnny Depp took to Instagram stories on Friday, May 12 to share the happy news with a sultry kiss pic. In the image, the 24-year-old sat in a chair and cradled her new GF’s face as she went in for a deep kiss. Lily-Rose wore her curly hair in a ponytail and rocked a sheer shirt, while 070 Shake wrapped her arm around her shoulder for the smooch.

item.title: Here's What Kate McKinnon Has Starred In Besides 'Saturday Night Live'
item.description: "Live from New York, it's Kate McKinnon!" McKinnon was born on January 6, 1984, in Sea Cliff, New York. She is an actress, comedian and writer best known for her time on Saturday Night Live (SNL), which she has been a part of since 2012 (she became an official cast member in 2013). The 38-year-old graduated from Columbia University in 2006 with a degree in theatre.The comedic actress has been nominated for the Emmy's nine times and has won twice- once in 2016 and again in 2017, both for SNL.

item.title: Lizzo Reveals Madame Tussauds Wax Figure
item.description: Lizzo has officially been immortalized in wax. TheGrammy Award-winning performer has revealed the first look at her Madame Tussauds wax figure ahead of its arrival at the Las Vegas museum. Lizzo wrote on Twitter that it was “single-handedly one of the most terrifyingly meta moments of my life,” sharing a video of her coming face-to-face with the statue. “Now I know what a twosome with Lizzo is like.” In one TikTok upload, she proclaimed the figure her “dupe” following a popular trend on the app.

item.description: Highlights Taylor Swift has written love songs for Travis Kelce, drawing inspiration from their relationship and falling in love together. Taylor and Travis' relationship is serious and filled with love and support, with both families approving of their romance. Taylor Swift is an incredibly prolific artist, and one of the reasons is because she finds inspiration in the people around her.

item.title: Watch Nicki Minajs Boyfriend Kenneth Petty Kiss Her Feet
item.description: A PDA-filled new year. Nicki Minaj kicked off 2019 by posting a video of her boyfriend, Kenneth “Zoo” Petty, kissing her feet in an outdoor hot tub. The “Chun-Li” rapper, 36, shared the intimate clip of Petty, 40, planting pecks across her toes on Instagram on Tuesday, January 1. The couple started off by relaxing in the bubbling water before Petty took Minaj’s legs in his hands and began kissing the soles of her feet as she giggled in enjoyment.
